<section class="methodology">
  <h2>Methodology</h2>

  <p>
    Walk-forward 5-fold backtesting on 2015&ndash;2024 MLB seasons (2020 excluded due to
    the shortened COVID season). Three model types are trained: Logistic Regression,
    Random Forest, and XGBoost. Two feature sets are evaluated: <strong>TEAM_ONLY</strong>
    (9 team-level features including Pythagorean win percentage, OPS, wOBA, bullpen ERA/FIP,
    park factor, and log5 baseline) and <strong>SP_ENHANCED</strong> (17 features including
    starting pitcher metrics after VIF multicollinearity pruning).
  </p>

  <p>
    All models are calibrated using isotonic regression per fold. No temperature scaling
    was needed&mdash;reliability diagrams confirmed that isotonic calibration produces
    well-calibrated probability estimates across the full range.
  </p>

  <p>
    The v2 SP_ENHANCED feature set adds K-BB%, WHIP, ERA, recent 30-day FIP, pitch count,
    and days rest&mdash;all computed as home-away differentials. VIF analysis removed 3
    multicollinear features (is_home, team_woba_diff, sp_siera_diff), leaving 17 features.
    SHAP importance analysis confirmed all 17 remaining features contribute meaningfully
    to predictions.
  </p>

  <p>
    Model probabilities are compared against Kalshi prediction market opening prices on the
    same 2025 game set. The best model (LR SP_ENHANCED, Brier 0.2331) outperforms the
    market (Brier 0.2434) by 0.0103 on 2,128 common games.
  </p>
</section>

